This paper is about neural abstractive text summarization, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of sequence-to-sequence models, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of pre-trained models and real-world applications, which are topics commonly discussed in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of headlines and summaries, which are topics commonly discussed in cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
